social_posts.post_text:
Hello! There are some new faces here, so if you’re new to my creative journey, welcome!

It’s been a while since I’ve done an intro! I am a visual artist, as well as a mother, midwife, educator, and healing arts practitioner. My mission is to nurture peace, enchantment, wonder, and wildness through botanical art, immersive courses, herbal wellness, and energy healing. 

I have always felt a sense of connection and communion with the living world. I have a special relationship with plants, and an affinity for being in, and holding, liminal space with others.

I’ve been a riot grrrl and a teen single parent. I’ve studied fine arts, French, and anthropology, and earned a PhD in gender, women’s, and sexuality studies. I’ve assisted hundreds of births as a midwife, and facilitated sacred space for hundreds more as a bodyworker and energy healer. 

I have a passion for helping others become more connected to the magic that is our earthly existence. I’m a sag sun, scorpio rising, pisces moon. 

I have always been a creator. My work in drawing, painting, and printmaking seeks to inspire a sense of wonder and oneness with the natural world. 

Right now I am welcoming folks into Tending the Light, an online journey into the heart of mindful wintering, which runs from winter solstice through spring equinox. 

It includes 15 weeks of guided meditations, yoga nidra, reflection exercises, embodiment practices, and community support, along with a Solstice Box full of handcrafted gifts to support rest, reflection, warmth, and enchantment. 

If this calls to you, you can find out more at the link in my bio, where you can also find my free guide to mindful wintering! 

Thank you for reading, and for being part of my world! 
.

.

I had no idea I was creating something so magical! I was thinking about the fern as a symbol of new beginnings when I decided on this design for the winter solstice candle holder. 

When I painted the first one, and lit the candle inside, I was surprised and delighted to see that it casts a magical snowflake shadow! 

What a lovely reminder that there is beauty in the cold winter snows, as well as the emerging new life that comes with return of the light. 

The simple act of lighting a candle in the darkness is so sacred and centering. This ritual is honestly one of my favorite things to do right now. Instant magic. 

✨This candle holder is part of the Solstice Box that’s included in my program Tending the Light, now open for enrollment! It’s an online journey into the heart of mindful wintering, which runs from winter solstice through spring equinox.

This gentle and supportive sanctuary includes 15 weeks of practices (guided meditations, yoga nidra, reflection exercises, embodiment practices) as well as community support, and a Solstice Box full of handcrafted gifts to support rest, reflection, warmth, and enchantment.

If this calls to you, you can find out more at the link in my bio, where you can also find my free guide to mindful wintering!

Japanese barberry. It was only through choosing to draw this plant that I looked it up and found out that this bush crowds out native plant species and provides an ideal environment for ticks! (As a person with chronic Lyme disease, it’s especially distressing that I have this in my yard!) So- I think this might need to be taken out this year - even though those red berries are so pretty against the snow. Thanks #lgperpetualjournal for inspiring me to always find out more about the plants in my environment!
.

I’m embarking on a project that’s been in my heart for a while: I am creating an oracle deck, called The Earth Speaks! For this deck, I am creating a series of 24 cards representing the ways in which the earth speaks to our spirits throughout the cycle of the seasons. 

🌿You are invited to be a part of the birth of this project through my new offering: The Forest. 

🌿The Forest includes a quarterly subscription box (with oracle cards released quarterly), monthly seasonal reflections and guided meditations, and exclusive writings and process photos illuminating the making of the cards and their meanings. I would love to have you join me! Link in ye olde bio 😘
.
.
.
.
.

Magnolia blossoms beckon - image for my oracle deck in process!
🌸
The message from the magnolias: You have an opportunity to give yourself to an experience of sensual beauty. You are being invited to slow down and say yes to what feels good. If there’s something you’re feeling called to do, but you worry about looking ridiculous, see what it might feel like to drop those inhibitions and let yourself have the experience. If there’s work you are approaching and you’re rushing, you might be missing the joyful parts of the process. Or maybe you’ve “arrived” at some desired outcome, and you’re forgetting to pause and let yourself bask in it. Let yourself be wild and free. Let yourself enjoy the simple pleasures. Open yourself to enjoying the gifts, the bounty, and the moments of magic life is offering you.

✨For first access to The Earth Speaks oracle, join me in my membership, The Forest! A space of devotion, offering oracle cards & stories, solstice & equinox boxes, monthly meditations, and seasonal reflections.
.
.
.

The Murmuration, Ink etching on clayboard, part of my collection The Earth Speaks, currently on display through the end of October @thejamestheater in Iowa City. 

Reception this Friday the 13th as part of the fall Gallery Walk! 

These illustrations represent the first half of a yearlong meditation on the spiritual-material connections between human lives and nature’s cycles, which will culminate in a deck of oracle cards.

A murmuration is an example of the concept of emergence: collective behavior in which a group does something together that the individual components of the system could not do alone.

A murmuration reminds us that we are individual beings who are also simultaneously connected to communities, and part of whole ecosystems that are much larger than ourselves. 

This oracle is a message to be responsive to the conditions around you. Tune in to your neighbors, community, and environment. Be ready to pivot, to dance, to improvise, to innovate. Find the joy in emergent activities, and contemplate your oneness with the universe.

Some of my favorite writers who reflect on murmuration and emergence: @adriennemareebrown and @mariapopova 

An affirmation: May we be responsive and co-creative with our surroundings. May we be aware of our simultaneous individuality and oneness with all that is. 
.

Monica Basile PhD (she/her) is a visual artist, Certified Professional Midwife, Reiki Master-Teacher, and professor of gender, women’s and sexuality studies. With more than 25 years of experience as a healer, midwife, and educator, she is passionate about helping people to experience beauty, enchantment, connection to the earth, and inner peace through honoring the seasonal and cyclical transformations of life. Her art practice currently focuses on botanical illustrations as meditations on the spiritual-material interconnectedness between humans and ecosystems. 

Monica is a mother and a longtime yoga and meditation practitioner. She believes in the power of gentle compassion, the wisdom of the body, and the light within all beings. Visit her at: ravenandmagnolia.com.
